description._content: Description: Aleppo Pine, part natural, part sown 10 years before. Behind it regrowth of Eastern Plane and Alder. All established after War Felling 1919 - 20. Troodos Forest, Elevation 3,400 feet above sea level. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: Aleppo Pines on left, Natural reproduction, many in centre from sowing at the end of 1921, Troodos Forest, Elevation 3,400 ft. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives.
